[1] Black streaked dwarf, undiagnosed diseases
Date: Sat 14 Aug 2010
Source: Viet Nam News (VNS) [edited]
<http://vietnamnews.vnagency.com.vn/Agriculture/202549/Pests-and-diseases-plague-rice-crops-.html>


Pests and diseases plague rice crops
------------------------------------
Pests and rice diseases have caused widespread damage to rice crops
in northern and central provinces. Changeable weather, including a
prolonged hot spell, had created favourable conditions, reported the
Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, and said that the
improper use of pesticides at the beginning of the crop had possibly
contributed to the situation.

Over 5200 ha [12 850 acres] of the rice crop in 19 northern
provinces, including Son La, Lao Cai, Dien Bien, Thai Binh, and Hai
Duong, had suffered from black stunt disease. In addition, the
summer-autumn crop had reportedly been hit by various pests.

Nghe An Agriculture and Rural Development Department said that local
farmers faced a high risk of crop loss because of drought and rice
diseases. Black streaked dwarf disease has also spread in 2300 ha
[5700 acres] over 11 districts.

At least 70 ha [173 acres] of paddy rice crop in northern Bac Giang
Province's Hiep Hoa District are suffering from an unidentified viral
disease that has made the rice leaves turn yellow and then red,
leaving the rice paddy withered. The district People's Committee said
that hundreds of hectares of paddy field was vulnerable to catching
the disease because of the high speed of contamination.

The locality witnessed the disease in the previous rice crop at the
same time in 2009 [when] it hit 600 ha [1483 acres] out of 8000 ha
[19 800 acres] of rice, reducing productivity by between 10-40
percent. Plant Protection Institute and Ha Noi Agriculture University
said laboratory tests found the disease was caused by a virus. More
exact findings would be released in the next 2 weeks.

