******
[2] Bacterial leaf streak, _Rice stripe virus_, undiagnosed disease
Date: Wed 11 Aug 2010
Source: Saigon Giai Phong (SGGP) Daily [edited]
<http://www.saigon-gpdaily.com.vn/National/Society/2010/8/84607/>


Diseases raging through farmers' crops
--------------------------------------
Farmers around the country have struggled with diseases killing their
rice crops, while the Government assistance has been low and specific
remedies have not been found.

In Hiep Hoa District in the northern province of Bac Giang, a farmer
uncovered over 500 square meters [5380 sq ft] of her rice fields had
a strange disease that made the rice turn saffron and unable to grow
properly. The disease, which stunted rice even though she sprayed
chemicals and fertilized the fields, spread widely frightening
farmers. The district People's Committee said that the disease is in
other communes as well, affecting thousands of households.

Meanwhile, in an adjacent commune farmers have seen the return of
another disease, which causes green fields to turn dull red with
black stripes along the veins of leaves. Agricultural University in
Hanoi have investigated and said it is bacterial streak disease. The
owner of 2000 square meters [21 500 sq ft] of 2-month old sick rice
fields said that last year [2009] his fields also contracted the
disease, forcing him to burn the fields, as his buffalos refused to
eat the sick rice.

In Thai Binh Province, the rice stripe virus has also plagued fields
in Tien Hai District. The rice stripe virus disease has rapidly
spread in the province and become an epidemic in northern provinces,
sending farmers racing to buy pesticides to save their crops.
Department of Plant Protection said that the Government has yet to
find specific remedies.

[Byline: Van Phuc Hau, trans. Bach Lien]

